.Im MicroEmacs modes
.so me.tni
.TH time 2m
.XI time - "File time stamping"
.SH NAME
time \- File time stamping
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "time Mode"
.sp
\fBt\fR \- mode line letter.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B time
mode, when enabled,  performs  automatic  time stamping of files on file write
operations. A time stamp string, defined by 
.Ht $timestamp 5 
is  searched  for in the  file  and  updated  with the  current  data and time
information, providing a record in the file of the last edit.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht buffer-mode 2 ,
.Ht global-mode 2 .
.Ht $timestamp 5 . 
.ad
.FH
